Selector is a program deflector (similar to objformat on DragonFly)

When executed, the Selector program will immediately execute a linker
program with the same arguments as a function of its name.

The Selector program will not be present on OmniOS, which is limited
to the Solaris linker.  Other platforms use Selector to switch between
GNU compatible linkers such as bfd, gold, mold, and lld.

The "LINKER" environment variable is used to specify which linker is
called.  If the variable is unset, raven.lld is selected if present,
otherwise ld.bfd is selected.

The linker expected in the toolchain are:
  - ld.bfd
  - ld.gold
  - raven.lld

The latter is not named ld.lld because /raven/toolchain/bin directory
is searched before /raven/bin directory.  We want /raven/bin/ld.lld
to be used if -fuse-ld=lld (or -fuse-ld=ld.lld) is specified.

If LINKER equals "mold", /raven/bin/ld.mold will be chosen.

If LINKER is set, but the linker is not found, a warning message will
be issues and ld.bfd will be selected instead.

The gcc ports will need to set LINKER in the build environment to
ensure ld.bfd builds the gcc ports.
